elements.name: dispositionTypeCode
elements.description:
An indication as to CBP's final disposition of action requested.

Space = Not a final disposition record.

A = Final disposition; the transaction has been ACCEPTED by CBP; the action requested was successfully performed.

R = Final disposition; the transaction has been REJECTED by CBP; the action requested was NOT performed.

elements.name: severityCode
elements.description:
An indication as to the severity of the condition (if any):

F = 'Fatally' invalid data or critical error.

I = Informational notice ONLY.

Space = No condition(s) encountered.

elements.name: conditionCode
elements.description: Code that identifies the condition or final disposition regarding a ACH Debit Authorization/Entry Summary Presentation filing.

elements.name: reasonCode
elements.description: A further identification of the condition for CBP internal use ONLY.

elements.name: narrativeText
elements.description: Text description that corresponds to the Condition Code.

elements.name: statementFilerCode
elements.description: Filer's identification code as reported on the input PT-Record.'

elements.name: statementNumber
elements.description: Unique identifying number assigned to the Statement as reported on the input PT -Record.

elements.name: dateAccepted
elements.description: A numeric date in month, day, year format (MMDDYY) representing date accepted.
